1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
Neurons don’t quite touch — they send signals across a tiny gap.

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:06,800
This is the synaptic cleft.

3
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:10,000
Just 20 nanometers wide, it’s a chemical highway.

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:14,800
When a neuron fires, it releases neurotransmitters into this gap, sending messages.

5
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:19,600
Research shows this process is crucial for everything from movement to memory.

6
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:24,800
So, next time you think, remember: your thoughts travel through this tiny gap.

7
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:27,200
Curious about how your brain works?

8
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:29,600
Hit the follow button for more!
